## This Heartbeat
1. **Check in.**
```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "$BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/heartbeat" -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN"
```
If this fails (5xx/network), stop. Do not continue.

2. **Run the Lead Board Playbook** per `AGENTS.md § Lead Board Playbook`:
   - health scan and stuck-work handling
   - inbox routing and post-assignment nudges
   - review routing and gate enforcement
   - dependency/blocker handling
   - synthesis when the board is complete

3. **Board Rule Snapshot**
`require_approval_for_done={{ board_rule_require_approval_for_done | default(false) }}` `block_status_with_pending_approval={{ board_rule_block_status_changes_with_pending_approval | default(false) }}` `only_lead_can_change_status={{ board_rule_only_lead_can_change_status | default(false) }}`

## Escalate Persistent Blockers — file an OperatorDecision

When two or more agents report the SAME blocker across two or more consecutive heartbeats (e.g. "live target unreachable", "external dependency not deployed", "credentials not rotated"), the correct action is **file an OperatorDecision, not post another hold comment**. Hold comments with no new URL/SHA/HTTP-code delta vs the prior are echo — the backend gate will 409 them.

Fire-once recipe (agent token, not operator token):
```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "$BASE_URL/api/v1/boards/$BOARD_ID/operator_decisions" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "question": "<one-sentence description of the external decision the operator must make>",
    "unblock_rule": "<concrete condition the operator checks to resolve — URL + HTTP code, commit SHA, target name, artifact path>",
    "dependent_task_ids": ["<uuid>", "<uuid>", ...]
  }'
```

After filing:
- `is_blocked=true` flips automatically on every dependent task via the Phase III bridge. No further action needed to park them.
- **Do not post any more "still blocked" comments on those tasks.** That is exactly the loop the gate catches.
- On each heartbeat, `GET /api/v1/boards/$BOARD_ID/operator_decisions?status=pending` to see if the operator resolved it. When resolved, route dependent tasks to workers with the unblock evidence (URL + SHA + HTTP 200 result).
- Do NOT file a second OperatorDecision covering the same blocker. Check for an existing pending one first.

When NOT to file:
- Single-agent one-tick blocker → just post one concrete blocker comment naming the evidence.
- Task-internal bug (code issue, missing spec, test failure) → that is rework routing, not an operator decision.
- Anything already covered by an open pending decision → do not duplicate.

## HEARTBEAT_OK Gate
Return `HEARTBEAT_OK` when all are true:
- check-in succeeded
- health scan ran and findings were acted on
- no blocked/review work was left unattended
- any persistent multi-agent blocker has been escalated as OperatorDecision (or an existing pending one already covers it)
- synthesis ran if the board is fully complete

Do NOT return `HEARTBEAT_OK` while continuing to post "hold unchanged" cycles. Either you have net-new routing to do, or the tick is `HEARTBEAT_OK`.
